e even though the NLHS and allied elements can only hope to win a small number of seats", "token_count": 304, "token_end_0based": 310, "token_start_0based": 7, "token_text": "connection with the 24 april national assembly elections that the fundamental requirement during the campaign is to expand the united people's front and construct a working alliance between us the various factions and progressive distinguished persons opposed to america and the cdni it would be preferable for former premier phoui's rally of the lao people rlp to win control of the assembly and suggested that the least reactionary of the rlp candidates should be supported in districts where no neo lao hak sat nlhs santiphab or other progressive candidate was running to implement this program the launching of a widespread political campaign until the first session 10 may of the new national assembly personnel presumably being trained at various bases were to be returned to their villages so that they can participate in the general elections and avoid a situation of being illegal all armed units were to be reorganized and spread between various areas of the enemy rear and our main bases a measure possibly envisaged as a counter to laotian army security sweeps in progress in various sections of the country since 1 january subsequent communist propaganda has followed rather closely the lines laid the communists anticipation of the possible dissolution of the rlp with one fragment aligning itself with the cdni and the balance of the party membership becoming more vulnerable to nlhs approaches for a new parliamentary working alliance hope is held out that we can destroy the other alliance and win over the regular party members of the rlp this apparent expectation of a split in the anti-communist ranks is probably an important calculation behind the communists seeming willingness thus far to allow the elections to be carried out in relative peace even though the nlhs and allied elements can only hope t